@NODE WHAT "What is it?"

  @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB} is a utility I wrote to test out Blitz Basic 2.1 that I'd
just bought.  I wanted a utility that would launch all the Internet programs
that I use, at the press of a key.  Its a fairly simple program, but I use
it daily, so thought I may as well release it in-case anyone finds it useful.

  There are no plans for any more versions.  However, if anyone finds this
utility genuinely useful, and would like to see some extra features, then
just EMail me and I will see what I can do.

@ENDNODE


@NODE INST "Installation details"

  To Install @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB} just double click the Install icon.

  However, you will need to manually configure the script file "Launch_ZFE":

  Here is a copy of the script - currently it is set-up for a Demon account, to
my post address.  Just change whatever paths you need, and of course your own
postal address, not mine!


;*** Launch script - connects to the Internet, fingers your
;*** post box and then runs ZFE's Internet

Execute SYS:AmiTCP/bin/StartNet
Link Up
CD SYS:AmiTCP/bin/

RUN Finger xtreme@post.demon.co.uk  ;enter your own postal address here

ZFE  ;enter the path for ZFE's Internet (ZFE) here (AmiTCP/bin/ is a good idea)

CD SYS:AmiTCP/bin/
Link Down
StopNet
EndCLI

@ENDNODE


@NODE USAGE "Usage"

  To use @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB}, install it to wherever you want it, and then
double click the Launch_ZFE icon (after manually configuring the script
file).  This will connect you to the Internet, fingers your post box and then
runs ZFE.  If you wish to try @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB} without connecting to the
Internet first, just execute the "ZFE" executable.

  Once @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB} is run, you will see there are eight buttons
(plus a status display and a Quit button).  These buttons launch the following
programs:

1. CLI  (keypress C)
2. EMail client (keypress E)
3. FTP client (keypress F)
4. IRC client (keypress I)
5. Lynx WWW browser (keypress L)
6. News reader (keypress N)
7. WWW browser (keypress W)

Plus one user configurable program (keypress rAMIGA + 1)

  To change the paths for these programs, press "P" or select "Preferences"
from the menu.  You will be presented by another window containing the paths
for all eight buttons, you can manually enter the paths here, or click on the
file gadget and select a file.  You must also enter the stack size that each
of the programs require in order to run (the default is 4096).  You can also
select a pattern for the window.

  These prefs can then be saved (they will be saved to the directory @{B}ZFE's Internet@{UB}
is installed in).

@ENDNODE


